msgstr "Sujets divers"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1647
#, no-c-format
msgid "Network transparency via KIO"
msgstr "Transparence réseau via KIO."

# Tag: title
#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1648
#, no-c-format
msgid "KIO-Slaves"
msgstr "KIO-Slaves"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1649
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The KIO library from &frameworks; supports network transparency via KIO-"
"slaves. &kdiff3; uses this for reading input files and for scanning folders. "
"This means that you can specify files and folders on local and remote "
"resources via &URL;s."
msgstr ""
"KDE supporte la transparence réseau via KIO. KDiff3 utilise cela pour lire "
"les fichiers en entrée ou scanner les dossiers. Cela signifie que vous "
"pouvez spécifier des fichiers et des dossiers locaux ou distants via des URL."

# Tag: para
#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1654
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "Exemple :"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1657
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<command>kdiff3</command> test.cpp  ftp://ftp.faraway.org/test.cpp\n"
#| "   <command>kdiff3</command> tar:/home/hacker/archive.tar.gz/dir ./dir"
msgid ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> test.cpp  ftp://ftp.faraway.org/test.cpp\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> tar:/home/hacker/archive.tar.gz/folder ./folder"
msgstr ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> test.cpp  ftp://ftp.faraway.org/test.cpp\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> tar:/home/hacker/archive.tar.gz/dos /dos"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1659
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first line compares a local file with a file on an &FTP; server. The "
"second line compares a folder within an compressed archive with a local "
"folder."
msgstr ""
"La première ligne compare un fichier local avec un fichier sur un serveur "
"&FTP;. La seconde compare un dossier contenu dans une archive compressée a "
"un dossier local."

# Tag: para
#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1661
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other KIO-slaves that are interesting are:"
msgstr "Les autres modules d'entrées / sorties intéressants sont :"

# Tag: para
#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1665
#, no-c-format
msgid "Files from the WWW (http:),"
msgstr "Fichiers depuis Internet (http : ),"

# Tag: para
#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1666
#, no-c-format
msgid "Files from the &FTP; (ftp:),"
msgstr "Fichiers depuis un &FTP; (ftp:),"

# Tag: para
#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1667
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encrypted file transfer (fish:, sftp:),"
msgstr "Transfert de fichier chiffré (fish ;, sftp :),"

# Tag: para
#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1668
#, no-c-format
msgid "&Windows; resources (smb:),"
msgstr "Ressources &Windows; (smb:),"

# Tag: para
#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1669
#, no-c-format
msgid "Local files (file:),"
msgstr "Fichiers locaux (file:),"

# Tag: para
#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1671
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other things that are possible, but probably less useful are:"
msgstr "D'autres choses sont possibles, mais probablement moins utiles sont :"

# Tag: para
#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1675
#, no-c-format
msgid "Man-pages (man:),"
